follow-up: Because the way you calculate late payments is dishonest. If I pay on the due date you treat it as a day late. If I pay 1 day after the due date, you count it as 31 days late. You even shut my gas off for being 14 days past due and refused to restoree the fee you charge for doing so when I called and explained this shouldn't have happened. And that is why you get reported as conducting unfair and predatory practices as a utility. 1 doesn't equal 31. Stuff happens - it shouldn't be the shut off penalty. After almost 20 years of service..really? We can't do this better? Thank you for allowing the feedback.
